  <!-- Section: FAQ -->
  <section id="faq" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is it really 0% personal income tax?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes. The UAE has no personal income tax—your salary, dividends, capital gains, and rental income are 100% yours. However, a 9% corporate tax was introduced in 2023 for business profits exceeding AED 375,000. Free zone companies may still qualify for 0% corporate tax if meeting substance requirements. Also note: US citizens must file US taxes regardless of residence.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I get UAE citizenship through the Golden Visa?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Generally, no. UAE citizenship is rarely granted to non-Emiratis. The Golden Visa provides indefinite renewable residence, but not a path to citizenship. Exceptional cases of citizenship are granted by royal decree to individuals who have made extraordinary contributions to the UAE—but this is rare and cannot be applied for. For most investors, permanent residence is the realistic goal.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What happens if I sell my property after getting the Golden Visa?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          If you sell your qualifying investment before the 10-year period ends, you lose your Golden Visa status. You must maintain the investment throughout. However, you can upgrade—buy a more expensive property, for example—as long as you remain above the threshold. Some investors buy additional properties while retaining the original qualifying investment.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How long can I stay outside the UAE?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Golden Visa holders can stay outside the UAE for up to 6 months without affecting their residence status. There's no minimum stay requirement—you don't need to live in the UAE full-time. This flexibility is one of the program's key advantages for investors who want a UAE base without committing to full-time residence.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I sponsor my family?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes. Golden Visa holders can sponsor their spouse, children (no age limit for female children; male children until they marry), and domestic staff (helpers, drivers). Each dependent needs their own health insurance policy. Dependent visas are processed after your Golden Visa is approved, typically within 1-2 weeks.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about banking and financial services?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          With your Emirates ID and Golden Visa, you can open UAE bank accounts, get credit cards, and access full financial services. Major banks include Emirates NBD, ADCB, FAB, and international banks (HSBC, Standard Chartered). UAE banking is modern, with excellent digital services. The UAE is also a crypto-friendly jurisdiction with regulated exchanges.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Final Verdict -->
  <section id="verdict" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Final Verdict</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      The UAE Golden Visa is the premier choice for investors who prioritize wealth preservation over citizenship. The combination of 10-year residence, 0% personal income tax, 100% business ownership, and world-class infrastructure is unmatched. No European or American program offers comparable tax treatment with this level of stability and development.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-4">
      The AED 2 million (~$545,000) investment threshold is significant but reasonable compared to the lifetime tax savings for high earners. At $300,000 annual income, you'll save $120,000+ per year in taxes compared to the US or UK—more than recovering the investment cost in 5 years while retaining the asset.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-6">
      The main limitations are the lack of citizenship path and high cost of living. If you need a second passport or prefer European lifestyle, look elsewhere. But if you want to maximize after-tax wealth accumulation in a stable, business-friendly jurisdiction with global connectivity, the UAE Golden Visa is hard to beat.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Bottom Line</h3>
      <p class="text-primary-800 mb-4">
        The UAE Golden Visa is ideal for high-net-worth investors and entrepreneurs who want tax-free income, long-term stability, and a strategic base between Europe and Asia—without needing a path to citizenship. Health insurance is mandatory—budget $3,000-8,000/year for comprehensive coverage. Work with qualified professionals for property and visa, and verify all requirements before committing.
      </p>
